  "text": "A total of 105 patients were analyzed in this study. For 61 cases (58.1%) the primary surgical approach was by laparotomy, 44 patients (41.9%) initially underwent laparoscopy. Detailed patient characteristics are listed in Table 1 . Patients in the laparotomy group were significantly older with a median age of 59 years (range 13-85 years) compared to 47 years (range 16-86 years) in the laparoscopy group (p = 0.006). Especially patients in the reproductive age (< 40 years) were more likely to receive primary laparoscopy (36.4% vs. [CITATION_1] .4%, p = 0.023).",
